Amalgamated Bank





Type

Private


Industry
Banking


Founded
April 14, 1923; 94 years ago (1923-04-14)


Headquarters
275 Seventh Avenue, New York City, New York, U.S.



Key people

Keith Mestrich, President & CEO



Net income

US$ 10.85 million (2016)


Total assets
US$ 4.055 billion (2016)


Total equity
US$ 341.78 million (2016)



Number of employees

392 (2017)[1]


Website
amalgamatedbank.com


Founded on April 14, 1923, by the Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America,[2] Amalgamated Bank is the largest union-owned bank[3] and one of the only unionized banks in the United States. Amalgamated Bank is currently majority-owned by Workers United, an SEIU Affiliate. As of June 30, 2015, Amalgamated Bank has nearly $4 billion in assets.[4] Through its Institutional Asset Management and Custody Division, Amalgamated Bank is one of the leading providers of investment and trust services to Taft-Hartley plans in the United States. As of June 30, 2015, the bank oversees approximately $40 billion in investment advisory and custodial services.
Amalgamated Bank provides affordable and accessible banking to its customers, advocates for workers’ rights, and promotes high standards of environmental, social and corporate governance practices. Amalgamated Bank clients include progressive individuals and organizations like presidential campaigns, labor unions and nonprofits.



